# Skipped Items Guidance

These code paths have intentionally-deferred follow-ups tracked in
[docs/follow-ups/skipped-items-roadmap.md](mdc:docs/follow-ups/skipped-items-roadmap.md).
Before making changes:

1. Read the relevant section in `skipped-items-roadmap.md` AND its
   cross-reference in `_skip_items_rca_v11.md`.
2. If a section says **"DO NOT do yet"**, respect it unless the user
   explicitly asks for that change with awareness of the deferral.
3. For plugin manifests: run
   `python scripts/audit_tool_classes.py --plugin <id>` and follow its
   suggestion when adding new tools (see also
   [plugin-tool-classes-howto.md](mdc:docs/plugin-tool-classes-howto.md)).
4. For lazy tool loading or sub-agent tool isolation, check whether
   the trigger conditions in §A.5 are met before making large
   structural changes; otherwise prefer the feature flag added in
   `Settings.effective_tools_main_chat_stable`.

## Quick reference table

| You are about to touch… | Read first |
|-------------------------|------------|
| `plugins/**/plugin.json` | §A.1 + audit script |
| `src/openakita/plugins/manifest.py` or `installer.py` | §A.2 (deferred validator stub) |
| `src/openakita/api/routes/_orgs_v2_legacy_redirects.py` | §A.3 (don't remove yet — observe `/api/diagnostics/legacy-shim-stats`) |
| `src/openakita/api/routes/orgs_v2.py::list_templates` | §A.4 (bare-array unification target) |
| `src/openakita/api/server.py` (shim `include_router`) | §A.3 |
| `apps/setup-center/src/api/orgs.ts` | §A.4 (frontend assumes runtime shape) |
| `core/_agent_legacy.py::_effective_tools` / `core/_brain_legacy.py::_convert_tools_to_llm` | §A.5 + `_skip_items_rca_v11.md` §1 |

## When in doubt

* Honour the **DO NOT do yet** notes.
* The roadmap file is the single source of truth — code-level TODOs
  link back to it, not the other way around.
* If you complete an item, move its section to `## Completed` in the
  roadmap (do not delete history).

See also: top-level `AGENTS.md` "Project evolution / open follow-ups".
